description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;“Journey to brilliant people”&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;“There has never been a more exciting time to join us!”&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Building on our innovative Trust People Strategy you will be contributing to our ambition of building brilliance for one and all. This includes enabling the development and talent management of every one of our colleagues as well as strong and positive collaboration with our partners and colleagues in Cornwall &amp; the Isles of Scilly.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Following investment in our infrastructure and a desire to increase expertise to make our People Strategy a reality, a number of new positions have become available which will help to ensure that we can proactively support our Care Groups to deliver Brilliant care to every one of our patients.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Trust is an awesome place to work, based within the beautiful county of Cornwall, which offers an outstanding quality of life and provides many opportunities for outdoor activities.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If now is the right time to make a move, come and join us on our journey and contribute to making the Royal Cornwall Hospitals NHS Trust the best place to work!&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;NameKerry Eldridge, Paul Hargreaves &amp; Helen LewisJob titleDirectors of People &amp; Organisational DevelopmentEmail addressrcht.podredesign@nhs.net&lt;/p&gt;
